featureSeries.name: E01 • It's About Time
featureSeries.about: When Mark Grayson finally inherits powers from his superhero father, it's a dream come true; however, there's more to being a hero than just choosing a name and costume.

featureSeries.name: E02 • Here Goes Nothing
featureSeries.about: With his father out of action, Mark struggles to defend the city against an inter-dimensional invasion by joining forces with a team of teenage superheroes.

featureSeries.name: E03 • Who You Calling Ugly?
featureSeries.about: Mark has to cut a study date short to help save Mount Rushmore from a crazed scientist; Robot assembles a new team of world-saving superheroes.

featureSeries.name: E04 • Episode 4
featureSeries.about: It's two firsts for Mark: a first date and a first trip to another planet; at the same time, Nolan and Debbie revisit their own first vacation together.

featureSeries.name: E05 • That Actually Hurt
featureSeries.about: Feeling confident in his new abilities, Mark risks a team-up with a local villain to take down a crime lord, while simultaneously juggling school and a new relationship.

featureSeries.name: E06 • You Look Kinda Dead
featureSeries.about: Mark joins William and Amber on a campus visit to Upstate University, hoping to discover a new future for himself; Debbie makes her own disturbing discovery.

featureSeries.name: E07 • We Need to Talk
featureSeries.about: Feeling lost and confused, Mark looks for advice from Eve; at the same time, everyone's looking for him.

featureSeries.name: E08 • Where I Really Come From
featureSeries.about: Mark must stop an unstoppable force to prove he's become the hero he's always wanted to be.
